Julianna Smoot has been named Deputy Assistant to the President and Social Secretary at the White House. She previously served as Chief of Staff for U.S. Trade Representative Ron Kirk. Smoot's appointment demonstrates the administration's commitment to creating an inclusive and culturally vibrant White House. Smoot expressed excitement about taking on the role and using her experience in building relationships with the international community. She is known for her organization and people skills, as well as her attention to detail, which are crucial for the responsibilities of the White House Social Secretary. Smoot has previously worked for the Obama Campaign and for Senators Schumer, Durbin, Reid, and Rockefeller.